        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35800",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Forgot to describe $result.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T09:30:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T09:30:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35804",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing the sort direction is a PHP-one-liner - I doubt it'll make sense to add another parameter to the already very long method signature of {{Zend_Ldap::search()}}. This functionality can easily be provided by user-land code.\r\n\r\nGenerall I like the idea of modifying the LDAP options properties' names but it won't be sufficient to provide this functionality in {{Zend_Ldap::search()}} - there are a lot more methods where a change would be necessary. I doubt that the work will be worth the effort as you won't gain anything new (LDAP attributes are case-insensitiv per se).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T10:04:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T10:04:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As you said, it's a trivial case.\r\n\r\nStill on the subject, i'd suggest that options should be in array. The reason is simple: if I need just some attributes, I'll need to fill every parameter till I get on attributes's parameter.\r\n\r\nConsidering that I'm not using any filters, default baseDn, default scope, I'll have to fill in three parameters till I get where I want.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\npublic function search($filter, $basedn = null, $scope = self::SEARCH_SCOPE_SUB,\r\n        array $attributes = array(), $sort = null, $sortDir = null, $resultChangeCase = null, $collectionClass = null)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAnd options being an array, you could consider my suggestions above. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T17:08:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T17:08:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35814",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The new way would look like:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\npublic function search(array(\r\n    'attributes' => array('displayname', 'cn', 'dn', 'departament', 'description')\r\n))\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nMuch easier :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-05T17:14:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-05T17:14:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35819",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Issue is reopened, but:\r\n\r\n- the option to change the attributes' names will not be added as the component favors lowercase attribute names in general\r\n- the option to reverse the sort direction cannot be added to {{Zend_Ldap::search()}} because the component relies solely on the LDAP server's capability to sort a result set. Results are retrieved sequentially from the server instead of instantiating the complete result set all at once. The option will be added {{to Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}} as the whole result set is available here.\r\n\r\nBoth {{to Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}} and {{Zend_Ldap::search()}} will be changed to accept an array parameter to remove the need to work through all the methods' parameters.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-06T03:36:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-06T03:36:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35820",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "fixed in trunk (r18883):\r\nadded {{$reverseSort}} argument to {{Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}}\r\nadded possibility to pass parameters to {{Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}} and {{Zend_Ldap::search()}} in a single array argument\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-06T04:06:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-06T04:06:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35822",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Couldn't you add the 'resultChangeCase' function on {{Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}} ?\r\n\r\nTreating results' case in the source ({{Zend_Ldap::searchEntries()}}) would be better than treat one by one later. Considering that most of AD servers' entries aren't standardized, I think that it's better all come in one single case format (lower or upper for me) and then work upon results.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about it ? :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=primolan",
                        "name": "primolan",
                        "displayName": "Rodrigo Novelo Primolan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-06T04:16:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-06T04:16:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35824",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attribute names are already normalized to lower-case. I think there is no need to add this option just for the sake of cosmetics. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sgehrig",
                        "name": "sgehrig",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Gehrig",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-06T04:48:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-06T04:48:24.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
